What is it?

A diamond price predictor application built around a linear regression model based on the dataset diamonds {ggplot2}, which contains the prices of almost 54,000 diamonds and their respective attributes.

How it works

  1. Diamonds attributes are selected, which filters the diamonds and a regression model is built to predict the price of diamonds with the selected color, cut and clarity. The model updates each time the selections are changed.

  2. The slider allows to vary the diamond weight (in carat) within the given range in the filtered dataset and evaluate the predicted price.

Server.R

library(shiny);library(ggplot2)library(dplyr)
function(input, output) {
  ds <- reactive({filter(diamonds, color == input$color & cut == input$cut)})
    output$clarity <-renderUI({selectInput("clarity","Clarity",
                                unique(select(ds(), clarity)))})
    ds1 <- reactive({ filter(ds(), clarity == input$clarity)})
    output$weight <- renderUI({sliderInput("carat","Carat:",min = min(select(ds1(),carat)),
                    max = max(select(ds1(),carat)) ,value = 1)})
    mdlpred <- reactive({fit <- lm(price ~ carat,data=ds1())
    weight <- input$carat ;predict(fit, newdata = data.frame(carat = weight))})
    output$plot <- renderPlot({weight <- input$carat
        g<- ggplot(data = ds1(),aes(x=carat,y=price))+theme_bw()+
            labs(x = "Weight of diamod (carat)", y = "Price in US dollars",
                 title="Linear Regression Model Fit")+
            geom_point(color="skyblue2", shape = 7, size=2)+
            geom_smooth(method = "lm",color="red")+
            geom_point(aes(x=weight, y=mdlpred()), color = "red", size= 4);g})
    output$pred <- renderText({round(mdlpred(),2)})
    output$stats <- renderPrint({fit <- lm(price ~carat,data = ds1())
        x<- summary(fit)[[4]][2,]; round(x,2)})}
